Saute steak in canola and sesame oil with ginger and garlic. Barely brown both sides of the meat. Add onions and red pepper. Cook for 2 minutes. Add sugar, stir constantly and allow to caramelize for a few seconds. Combine Soya sauce, wine, vinegar, cornstarch and chili flakes. Add to stir-fry. Bring mixture to a boil. Serve immediately.